# Development Rules for Generic SaaS Project

## Build and Compilation Rules
- **ALWAYS build and compile after making code changes**
- Run `npm run build` for frontend changes to catch TypeScript errors
- Run `npm run lint` to check code quality and fix issues
- Fix compilation errors immediately before considering task complete
- Test the application after major changes

## Code Quality Rules
- Update gitignore when needed
- When using python, update requirements.txt when a new package is used
- Add useful comments for important features
- Generic components should not be tied to a single object type
- Use proper TypeScript types instead of `any` where possible
- Remove console.log statements in production code

## UI/UX Rules
- Maintain consistent spacing and layout
- Implement proper loading and error states
- Persist user preferences (like column visibility) in localStorage
- Provide clear visual feedback for user actions
- Ensure accessibility with proper ARIA labels and keyboard navigation